events.description: Constantine the Great enters Rome after his victory at the Battle of the Milvian Bridge, stages a grand adventus in the city, and is met with popular jubilation. Maxentius' body is fished out of the Tiber and beheaded.
events.html: • 312 – Constantine the Great enters Rome after his victory at the Battle of the Milvian Bridge, stages a grand adventus in the city, and is met with popular jubilation. Maxentius' body is fished out of the Tiber and beheaded.

events.description: Valentinian III, Western Roman Emperor, marries Licinia Eudoxia, daughter of his cousin Theodosius II, Eastern Roman Emperor in Constantinople unifying the two branches of the House of Theodosius.
events.html: • 437 – Valentinian III, Western Roman Emperor, marries Licinia Eudoxia, daughter of his cousin Theodosius II, Eastern Roman Emperor in Constantinople unifying the two branches of the House of Theodosius.

events.description: First trial for witchcraft in Paris leading to the death of three people.
events.html: • 1390 – First trial for witchcraft in Paris leading to the death of three people.

events.description: Battle of Brustem: Charles the Bold defeats Prince-Bishopric of Liège.
events.html: • 1467 – Battle of Brustem: Charles the Bold defeats Prince-Bishopric of Liège.

events.description: Russian homage to the King of Poland, Sigismund III Vasa.
events.html: • 1611 – Russian homage to the King of Poland, Sigismund III Vasa.

events.description: The London Pageant of 1621 celebrates the inauguration of Edward Barkham (Lord Mayor).
events.html: • 1621 – The London Pageant of 1621 celebrates the inauguration of Edward Barkham (Lord Mayor).[1]

events.description: Second Northern War: Naval forces of the Dutch Republic defeat the Swedes in the Battle of the Sound.
events.html: • 1658 – Second Northern War: Naval forces of the Dutch Republic defeat the Swedes in the Battle of the Sound.

events.description: Portuguese forces defeat the Kingdom of Kongo and decapitate King António I of Kongo, also known as Nvita a Nkanga.
events.html: • 1665 – Portuguese forces defeat the Kingdom of Kongo and decapitate King António I of Kongo, also known as Nvita a Nkanga.

events.description: Leibniz makes the first use of the long s (∫) as a symbol of the integral in calculus.
events.html: • 1675 – Leibniz makes the first use of the long s (∫) as a symbol of the integral in calculus.

events.description: Mount Hood (Oregon) is named after Samuel Hood, 1st Viscount Hood by Lt. William E. Broughton who sighted the mountain near the mouth of the Willamette River.
events.html: • 1792 – Mount Hood (Oregon) is named after Samuel Hood, 1st Viscount Hood by Lt. William E. Broughton who sighted the mountain near the mouth of the Willamette River.

events.description: Eighteen countries meet in Geneva and agree to form the International Red Cross.
events.html: • 1863 – Eighteen countries meet in Geneva and agree to form the International Red Cross.[2]

entities.name: International Committee of the Red Cross

events.description: American Civil War: Battle of Wauhatchie: Forces under Union General Ulysses S. Grant repel a Confederate attack led by General James Longstreet in one of the few night battles of the war, protecting the Union's recently opened supply line into Chattanooga, Tennessee.
events.html: • 1863 – American Civil War: Battle of Wauhatchie: Forces under Union General Ulysses S. Grant repel a Confederate attack led by General James Longstreet in one of the few night battles of the war, protecting the Union's recently opened supply line into Chattanooga, Tennessee.[3]

events.description: The Convention of Constantinople is signed, guaranteeing free maritime passage through the Suez Canal during war and peace.
events.html: • 1888 – The Convention of Constantinople is signed, guaranteeing free maritime passage through the Suez Canal during war and peace.[4]

events.description: Ottoman entry into World War I.
events.html: • 1914 – Ottoman entry into World War I.[5]

entities.name: Ottoman entry into World War I

events.description: The German High Seas Fleet is incapacitated when sailors mutiny, an action which would trigger the German Revolution of 1918–19.
events.html: • 1918 – The German High Seas Fleet is incapacitated when sailors mutiny, an action which would trigger the German Revolution of 1918–19.

events.description: United States: Second trial of Sacco and Vanzetti in Boston, Massachusetts.
events.html: • 1921 – United States: Second trial of Sacco and Vanzetti in Boston, Massachusetts.

events.description: Turkey becomes a republic following the dissolution of the Ottoman Empire.
events.html: • 1923 – Turkey becomes a republic following the dissolution of the Ottoman Empire.[6]

events.description: Black Tuesday: The New York Stock Exchange crashes, ending the Great Bull Market of the 1920s and beginning the Great Depression.
events.html: • 1929 – Black Tuesday: The New York Stock Exchange crashes, ending the Great Bull Market of the 1920s and beginning the Great Depression.[7]

events.description: The Holocaust: In the Kaunas Ghetto, over 10,000 Jews are shot by German occupiers at the Ninth Fort, a massacre known as the "Great Action".
events.html: • 1941 – The Holocaust: In the Kaunas Ghetto, over 10,000 Jews are shot by German occupiers at the Ninth Fort, a massacre known as the "Great Action".[8]

events.description: The Holocaust: In the United Kingdom, leading clergymen and political figures hold a public meeting to register outrage over Nazi Germany's persecution of Jews.
events.html: • 1942 – The Holocaust: In the United Kingdom, leading clergymen and political figures hold a public meeting to register outrage over Nazi Germany's persecution of Jews.

events.description: The Dutch city of Breda is liberated by 1st Polish Armoured Division.
events.html: • 1944 – The Dutch city of Breda is liberated by 1st Polish Armoured Division.

events.description: World War II: The Soviet Red Army enters Hungary.
events.html: • 1944 – World War II: The Soviet Red Army enters Hungary.

events.description: Israeli-Palestinian conflict: Safsaf massacre: Israeli soldiers capture the Palestinian village of Safsaf in the Galilee; afterwards, between 52 and 64 villagers are massacred by the IDF.
events.html: • 1948 – Israeli-Palestinian conflict: Safsaf massacre: Israeli soldiers capture the Palestinian village of Safsaf in the Galilee; afterwards, between 52 and 64 villagers are massacred by the IDF.

events.description: BCPA Flight 304 DC-6 crashes near San Francisco.
events.html: • 1953 – BCPA Flight 304 DC-6 crashes near San Francisco.[9]

events.description: The Soviet battleship Novorossiysk strikes a World War II mine in the harbor at Sevastopol.
events.html: • 1955 – The Soviet battleship Novorossiysk strikes a World War II mine in the harbor at Sevastopol.[10]

events.description: Suez Crisis begins: Israeli forces invade the Sinai Peninsula and push Egyptian forces back toward the Suez Canal.
events.html: • 1956 – Suez Crisis begins: Israeli forces invade the Sinai Peninsula and push Egyptian forces back toward the Suez Canal.[11]

events.description: Israel's prime minister David Ben-Gurion and five of his ministers are injured when Moshe Dwek throws a grenade into the Knesset.
events.html: • 1957 – Israel's prime minister David Ben-Gurion and five of his ministers are injured when Moshe Dwek throws a grenade into the Knesset.[12]

events.description: An airplane carrying the Cal Poly football team crashes on takeoff in Toledo, Ohio.
events.html: • 1960 – An airplane carrying the Cal Poly football team crashes on takeoff in Toledo, Ohio.[13]

entities.name: California Polytechnic State University football team plane crash

events.description: The United Republic of Tanganyika and Zanzibar is renamed to the United Republic of Tanzania.
events.html: • 1964 – The United Republic of Tanganyika and Zanzibar is renamed to the United Republic of Tanzania.[14]

events.description: Biggest jewel heist; involving the Star of India in the American Museum of Natural History in New York City by Murph the Surf and gang.
events.html: • 1964 – Biggest jewel heist; involving the Star of India in the American Museum of Natural History in New York City by Murph the Surf and gang.[15]

events.description: Montreal's World Fair, Expo 67, closes with over 50 million visitors.
events.html: • 1967 – Montreal's World Fair, Expo 67, closes with over 50 million visitors.[16]

events.description: The first-ever computer-to-computer link is established on ARPANET, the precursor to the Internet.
events.html: • 1969 – The first-ever computer-to-computer link is established on ARPANET, the precursor to the Internet.[17]

events.description: The three surviving perpetrators of the Munich massacre are released from prison in exchange for the hostages of the hijacked Lufthansa Flight 615.
events.html: • 1972 – The three surviving perpetrators of the Munich massacre are released from prison in exchange for the hostages of the hijacked Lufthansa Flight 615.[18]

events.description: Demonstration flight of a secretly modified C-130 for an Iran hostage crisis rescue attempt ends in a crash landing at Eglin Air Force Base's Duke Field, Florida, leading to the cancellation of Operation Credible Sport.
events.html: • 1980 – Demonstration flight of a secretly modified C-130 for an Iran hostage crisis rescue attempt ends in a crash landing at Eglin Air Force Base's Duke Field, Florida, leading to the cancellation of Operation Credible Sport.

events.description: Major General Samuel K. Doe is announced as the winner of the first multi-party election in Liberia.
events.html: • 1985 – Major General Samuel K. Doe is announced as the winner of the first multi-party election in Liberia.

events.description: British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher opens the last stretch of the M25 motorway.
events.html: • 1986 – British Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher opens the last stretch of the M25 motorway.

events.description: The American Galileo spacecraft makes its closest approach to 951 Gaspra, becoming the first probe to visit an asteroid.
events.html: • 1991 – The American Galileo spacecraft makes its closest approach to 951 Gaspra, becoming the first probe to visit an asteroid.[19]

events.description: Francisco Martin Duran fires over two dozen shots at the White House; he is later convicted of trying to kill U.S. President Bill Clinton.
events.html: • 1994 – Francisco Martin Duran fires over two dozen shots at the White House; he is later convicted of trying to kill U.S. President Bill Clinton.[20]

events.description: In South Africa, the Truth and Reconciliation Commission presents its report, which condemns both sides for committing atrocities.
events.html: • 1998 – In South Africa, the Truth and Reconciliation Commission presents its report, which condemns both sides for committing atrocities.[21]

events.description: Space Shuttle Discovery blasts off on STS-95 with 77-year-old John Glenn on board, making him the oldest person to go into space at that time.
events.html: • 1998 – Space Shuttle Discovery blasts off on STS-95 with 77-year-old John Glenn on board, making him the oldest person to go into space at that time.[22]

events.description: ATSC HDTV broadcasting in the United States is inaugurated with the launch of the STS-95 space shuttle mission.
events.html: • 1998 – ATSC HDTV broadcasting in the United States is inaugurated with the launch of the STS-95 space shuttle mission.[23]

events.description: Hurricane Mitch, the second deadliest Atlantic hurricane in history, makes landfall in Honduras.
events.html: • 1998 – Hurricane Mitch, the second deadliest Atlantic hurricane in history, makes landfall in Honduras.[24]

events.description: The Gothenburg discothèque fire in Sweden kills 63 and injures over 200.
events.html: • 1998 – The Gothenburg discothèque fire in Sweden kills 63 and injures over 200.[25]

events.description: A large cyclone devastates Odisha, India.
events.html: • 1999 – A large cyclone devastates Odisha, India.[26]

events.description: A fire destroys a luxurious department store in Ho Chi Minh City, where 1,500 people are shopping. More than 60 people die and over 100 are unaccounted for in the deadliest peacetime disaster in Vietnam.

events.description: The Arabic-language news network Al Jazeera broadcasts an excerpt from a 2004 Osama bin Laden video in which the terrorist leader first admits direct responsibility for the September 11, 2001 attacks and references the 2004 U.S. presidential election.
events.html: • 2004 – The Arabic-language news network Al Jazeera broadcasts an excerpt from a 2004 Osama bin Laden video in which the terrorist leader first admits direct responsibility for the September 11, 2001 attacks and references the 2004 U.S. presidential election.[28]

events.description: Bombings in Delhi, India kill 67 and injure over 200 people.
